The paper presents an approach to building natural language interfaces to databases using neural sequence models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The approach also involves improving the performance of the models based on user feedback, which involves database-specific engineering (cs.DB) and machine learning techniques (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of crowd annotations to improve the models, which falls under the category of human computation (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
